## 6. How to frame this as an invention

Key points to emphasize in documentation / a draft patent / writeup:

- **Global error‑budgeted variable quantization**:
  - Bit‑widths and quantizers selected under an explicit global constraint on perplexity, not uniform per‑layer heuristics.
- **Joint treatment of weights, KV cache, and high‑precision islands**:
  - Single optimization that decides which parts stay high‑precision, including KV cache, based on measured PPL impact. [arxiv](https://arxiv.org/html/2411.02530v1)
- **Runtime designed for VRAM‑independent deployment**:
  - All quantization and layout choices optimized for host‑RAM storage + streaming to a small compute accelerator (or CPU‑only).
- **Automatic profiling‑driven allocation**:
  - Data‑driven sensitivity analysis that maps local quantization choices to global perplexity impact on a calibration set.

Even though the components (GPTQ, AWQ, KV‑cache quantization) exist, this particular combination—error‑budgeted, global, variable bit allocation explicitly targeting “full host RAM, no VRAM residency”—is novel enough to be interesting if you push it through experiments on Qwen 35B and maybe one more family (e.g. Llama 3.1 70B). [jarvislabs](https://jarvislabs.ai/blog/vllm-quantization-complete-guide-benchmarks)

